Harley shares fall sharply on weak sales
Harley-Davidson Inc. shares fell sharply on plans to make and ship fewer motorcycles this year amid a sharp drop in retail sales. The Milwaukee-based manufacturer said Tuesday that world-wide retail sales fell 7% in the second quarter. Sales fell 9% in the U.S., Harley's largest market. Harley's shares fell as much as 11% on the news.

Jul. 18, 2017 at 1:29 p.m. ET
by MarketWatch.com










Here’s why some say it’s time to tread carefully with Netflix shares

